Currently, through the web interface, administrators can view the list of restricted pages in a given space.

If this functionality were exposed through (for example) a new method in the remote API, then users implementing remote searches could get the list of pages their privileged search indexing accounts can't index, and notify a human administrator.

Currently, if administrators know the ID of a restricted page, they can already view it and perform other operations on it via the Remote API, this change would simply give them a list of restricted pages to supplement the filtered list returned by the getPages method.

